6
7
8 An Act relating to public health; requiring primary
health care providers to offer pediatric screenings
9 for type 1 diabetes subject to certain conditions;
providing for certain reimbursement; directing the
10 State Department of Health to seek certain funding;
directing promulgation of rules; providing for
11 codification; and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-581 of Title 63, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Every primary health care provider in this state shall offer
19 pediatric screenings for type 1 diabetes in accordance with accepted
20 medical practices and rules promulgated by the State Commissioner of
21 Health and subject to the informed consent of the child’s parent or
22 legal guardian.
23
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1427 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 B. The screenings described in subsection A of this section
2 shall be reimbursable under the state Medicaid program, subject to
3 receipt of any necessary federal approval.
4 C. The State Department of Health shall seek grants and other
5 funding opportunities to support the provision of pediatric
6 screenings for type 1 diabetes as described in subsection A of this
7 section.
8 D. 1. The State Commissioner of Health shall promulgate rules
9 necessary to implement the provisions of this section.
10 2. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority Board shall promulgate
11 rules necessary to implement subsection B of this section.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
13 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
February 16, 2026 - DO PASS AS AMENDED
